      "comment_id" : 7703785,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Java int type is 4 bytes long. According to android.graphics.Color&#39;s documentation, the leftest byte is the alpha channel. By using a bit wise AND operation with the value 0x00FFFFFF, you essentially clears the leftest byte (alpha channel) to 0.  When used with Integer.toHexString, it&#39;ll just leave the rest of the 3 bytes in String.  All non-significant digits will be dropped from the call, so if you want the leading zeroes, you may have to prepend that in yourself."
